abstract: Democratic presidential hopefuls fanned out across the United States on Sunday to try blunt Bernie Sanders' momentum after a dominant victory in Nevada solidified his front-runner status ahead of 15 key nominating contests in the next 10 days.
snippet: Democratic presidential hopefuls fanned out across the United States on Sunday to try blunt Bernie Sanders' momentum after a dominant victory in Nevada solidified his front-runner status ahead of 15 key nominating contests in the next 10 days.
lead_paragraph: NORTH CHARLESTON, S.C. — Democratic presidential hopefuls fanned out across the United States on Sunday to try blunt Bernie Sanders' momentum after a dominant victory in Nevada solidified his front-runner status ahead of 15 key nominating contests in the next 10 days.
headline_main: Democratic Rivals Try to Slow Sanders After Big Nevada Win
headline_print_headline: Democratic Rivals Try to Slow Sanders After Big Nevada Win

abstract: Bernie Sanders' convincing win in the Nevada caucuses signaled his campaign is gathering strength and reaching voters who had previously eluded him, putting him on a path – for now – toward the Democratic presidential nomination.
snippet: Bernie Sanders' convincing win in the Nevada caucuses signaled his campaign is gathering strength and reaching voters who had previously eluded him, putting him on a path – for now – toward the Democratic presidential nomination.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Bernie Sanders' convincing win in the Nevada caucuses signaled his campaign is gathering strength and reaching voters who had previously eluded him, putting him on a path – for now – toward the Democratic presidential nomination.
headline_main: Sanders' Big Nevada Win Narrows Rivals' Path to Democratic Nomination
headline_print_headline: Sanders' Big Nevada Win Narrows Rivals' Path to Democratic Nomination

abstract: A burn-it-down candidate is topping a splintered field of more moderate contenders and setting the party’s establishment wing on edge.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A burn-it-down candidate is topping a splintered field of more moderate contenders and setting the party’s establishment wing on edge.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren rallied a rowdy crowd in Seattle Saturday night as ballots for Washington state's March 10 presidential primary began arriving in mailboxes of the state’s nearly 4.5 million voters.

lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren rallied a rowdy crowd in Seattle Saturday night as ballots for Washington state's March 10 presidential primary began arriving in mailboxes of the state’s nearly 4.5 million voters.

abstract: There’s the democracy-in-action proselytizer, the resigned skeptic and the thoroughly bewildered. All made their way to Coronado High School in Nevada to help pick a presidential nominee.
snippet: There’s the democracy-in-action proselytizer, the resigned skeptic and the thoroughly bewildered. All made their way to Coronado High School in Nevada to help pick a presidential nominee.
lead_paragraph: HENDERSON, Nev. — One voter was under the mistaken impression that he had come to a primary, not a caucus. Another had planned to vote for former New York mayor Michael R. Bloomberg, only to discover he was not on the ballot. And a third had a multipart procedural question for the volunteer running his precinct caucus at Coronado High School.

abstract: After the chaos of the Iowa caucuses, Democrats were desperate to avoid another fiasco in Nevada. And early indications Saturday were that they succeeded.
snippet: After the chaos of the Iowa caucuses, Democrats were desperate to avoid another fiasco in Nevada. And early indications Saturday were that they succeeded.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — After the chaos of the Iowa caucuses, Democrats were desperate to avoid another fiasco in Nevada. And early indications Saturday were that they succeeded.

headline_main: Why Are Nevada Caucus Results Coming in So Slowly?

abstract: Nevada caucus officials and voters at multiple sites on Saturday reported voting rules confusion, calculation glitches and delays in reporting tallies - despite efforts to avoid the issues that plagued Iowa's caucuses earlier this month.
snippet: Nevada caucus officials and voters at multiple sites on Saturday reported voting rules confusion, calculation glitches and delays in reporting tallies - despite efforts to avoid the issues that plagued Iowa's caucuses earlier this month.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Nevada caucus officials and voters at multiple sites on Saturday reported voting rules confusion, calculation glitches and delays in reporting tallies - despite efforts to avoid the issues that plagued Iowa's caucuses earlier this month.
headline_main: Slow Results, Confusion and Complaints at Nevada Caucus Sites
headline_print_headline: Slow Results, Confusion and Complaints at Nevada Caucus Sites

abstract: A multiracial coalition brought the senator’s long-promised political revolution to vivid life, for perhaps the first time in the 2020 race.
snippet: A multiracial coalition brought the senator’s long-promised political revolution to vivid life, for perhaps the first time in the 2020 race.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — They showed up to Desert Pines High School in Tío Bernie T-shirts to caucus on Saturday morning, motivated by the idea of free college tuition, “Medicare for all” and the man making those promises: a 78-year-old white senator from Vermont. To dozens of mostly working-class Latinos, Bernie Sanders seemed like one of their own, a child of immigrants who understands what it means to be seen as a perpetual outsider.
